<node id="Attachment 0200000">
  <data key="d0">Attachment 0200000</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment 0200000 is an integral component of the Request for Proposal (RFP) document. It is referred to specifically within the RFP section and serves as a worksheet tab under Section J-0200000, which is part of the larger RFP document.

This attachment contains additional details pertaining to specific lines of the proposal. Notably, it includes information related to CLIN 0019 for the 6th period optimal resource work (RW) and CLIN 0027. As a component within the RFP Section J-0200000, Attachment 0200000 is part of the RFP document, providing supplementary information to aid in the proposal process.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-47c5b16ca68b3ce4da8cf59d700a0552&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e50bf4d58079ccb2c1fb7cb05ca6f201&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1134bde47b2e4250302b40f0cd197b50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6f6d7ee5e904366a5f727d9c8e9b5ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6452d63d89da4803c08bf42cdbc18f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-195f0b6d0eb8978e12a550de5227f088&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea26fde1901b2f6713654fee35033196&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a65e507c3cadde9b847528f2bfcba271&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88ec1d25f6b9d47e8bbd18881f0734e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0ec534cedde816f134ee4c2df639f3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ce2548337b8b7064fd3aa28ee4dd105&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9d1afdb404d508b4795d2d97f0a9440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8459283e38daefcdf466872389b2a66e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9688477020b78bd66f295fe2e7018cdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04a2b8ffa2a50c16761439fbed0b449c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759451589</data>
</node>
<node id="Firm Fixed Price">
  <data key="d0">Firm Fixed Price</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Firm Fixed Price (FFP) is a pricing method widely used in contract work, particularly for projects with clearly defined scopes. In this arrangement, the buyer and seller agree upon a fixed price for the goods or services prior to commencing the project. This agreed-upon total cost remains constant throughout the project lifecycle, regardless of fluctuations in production costs or potential overruns. FFP contracts are typically used when there is sufficient certainty about the work's requirements, allowing for accurate estimation and pricing. The contractor assumes the risk associated with any additional costs that may arise during the project execution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0032ac1505bc8aa343a800ceff232e28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47c5b16ca68b3ce4da8cf59d700a0552&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6f6d7ee5e904366a5f727d9c8e9b5ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea26fde1901b2f6713654fee35033196&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88ec1d25f6b9d47e8bbd18881f0734e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0ec534cedde816f134ee4c2df639f3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9d1afdb404d508b4795d2d97f0a9440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8459283e38daefcdf466872389b2a66e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe624ef1696bb45188aad740d8ca4adb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61cd65d989970185b729effedefbd4e1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759451598</data>
</node>
